# Inventory Management API

A production-oriented **ASP.NET Core Web API** built with **Clean Architecture**, **Vertical Slice Architecture**, **CQRS + MediatR**, **ASP.NET Identity**, **JWT Authentication**, **Refresh Token Rotation**, **Serilog**, and **Docker**.

The project focuses on maintainability, scalability, and modern backend development practices rather than a simple CRUD implementation.

---

## Features

### Architecture

* Clean Architecture
* Vertical Slice Architecture
* CQRS with MediatR
* Repository Pattern
* Dependency Injection
* FluentValidation Pipeline Behavior

### Authentication & Authorization

* ASP.NET Identity
* JWT Authentication
* Refresh Token Rotation
* Policy-based Authorization

### Inventory Workflows

* Product, category, supplier, and customer management
* Stock ledger with damage, adjustment, and reversal movements
* Purchase draft, edit, post, and cancel lifecycle
* Delivery challan draft, edit, post, and cancel lifecycle
* Direct sales invoices and invoices created from posted challans
* Customer payments and payment reversals
* Customer and supplier returns
* Current stock, ledger, register, and gross profit reports

### Logging & Error Handling

* Global Exception Middleware
* Structured Logging with Serilog
* Console and File Logging

### Database

* Entity Framework Core
* SQLite
* Automatic EF Core Migrations on Startup

### DevOps

* Multi-stage Docker Build
* Docker Compose
* Persistent Database Volume
* Persistent Log Volume

---

## Workflow Rules

Documents are created as drafts where applicable. Drafts do not change stock or balances.

* Posting a purchase increases stock and updates weighted-average cost.
* Posting a delivery challan decreases stock without creating customer debt.
* Posting a direct sales invoice decreases stock and updates customer debt.
* Invoicing posted challans does not reduce stock a second time.
* Posting returns applies the corresponding stock and balance effects.
* Cancelling posted documents preserves history through reversal movements.
* Gross profit uses historical costs stored with sales and returns, not the product's current average cost.

---

## API Overview

All routes except authentication require a bearer access token. Swagger provides complete request and response schemas.

### Authentication and Master Data

| Area | Routes |
| --- | --- |
| Authentication | `POST /api/Auth/Register`, `/api/Auth/Login`, `/api/Auth/RefreshToken` |
| Products | `/api/products` |
| Categories | `/api/categories` |
| Suppliers | `/api/suppliers` |
| Customers | `/api/customers` |
| Stock ledger | `GET /api/stock-movements` |
| Manual corrections | `POST /api/stock-movements/damage`, `/adjustment`, `/{id}/reverse` |

### Purchases

| Method | Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `GET` | `/api/purchases` | List purchases with paging and filters |
| `GET` | `/api/purchases/{id}` | Get a purchase |
| `POST` | `/api/purchases` | Create a draft |
| `PUT` | `/api/purchases/{id}` | Edit a draft |
| `POST` | `/api/purchases/{id}/post` | Receive stock |
| `POST` | `/api/purchases/{id}/cancel` | Cancel or reverse a purchase |

### Delivery Challans

| Method | Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `GET` | `/api/delivery-challans` | List challans with paging and filters |
| `GET` | `/api/delivery-challans/{id}` | Get a challan |
| `POST` | `/api/delivery-challans` | Create a draft |
| `PUT` | `/api/delivery-challans/{id}` | Edit a draft |
| `POST` | `/api/delivery-challans/{id}/post` | Issue stock |
| `POST` | `/api/delivery-challans/{id}/cancel` | Cancel or reverse a challan |

### Sales Invoices

| Method | Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `GET` | `/api/sales-invoices` | List invoices with paging and filters |
| `GET` | `/api/sales-invoices/{id}` | Get an invoice |
| `POST` | `/api/sales-invoices` | Create a draft direct invoice |
| `POST` | `/api/sales-invoices/from-challans` | Create an invoice from posted challan items |
| `PUT` | `/api/sales-invoices/{id}` | Edit a draft direct invoice |
| `POST` | `/api/sales-invoices/{id}/post` | Post a direct invoice |
| `POST` | `/api/sales-invoices/{id}/cancel` | Cancel an invoice |

### Payments

| Method | Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `GET` | `/api/payments` | List customer payments |
| `POST` | `/api/payments` | Record a payment |
| `POST` | `/api/payments/{id}/reverse` | Reverse a payment |

### Returns

| Method | Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `GET` | `/api/customer-returns/{id}` | Get a customer return |
| `POST` | `/api/customer-returns` | Create a draft customer return |
| `POST` | `/api/customer-returns/{id}/post` | Post a customer return |
| `POST` | `/api/customer-returns/{id}/cancel` | Cancel a customer return |
| `GET` | `/api/supplier-returns/{id}` | Get a supplier return |
| `POST` | `/api/supplier-returns` | Create a draft supplier return |
| `POST` | `/api/supplier-returns/{id}/post` | Post a supplier return |
| `POST` | `/api/supplier-returns/{id}/cancel` | Cancel a supplier return |

### Reports

| Route | Filters and result |
| --- | --- |
| `GET /api/inventory-reports/current-stock` | Paged stock by category, search text, and quantity filter |
| `GET /api/inventory-reports/products/{productId}/ledger` | Paged stock history by date and movement type |
| `GET /api/inventory-reports/purchase-register` | Purchases and summary by date, supplier, product, and status |
| `GET /api/inventory-reports/sales-register` | Sales and summary by date, customer, product, source, and status |
| `GET /api/inventory-reports/gross-profit` | Revenue, cost of goods sold, returns, and gross profit |

Paged endpoints use `pageNumber` and `pageSize`.

